HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 371
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Major Richard Wayne
Brandt of Ooltewah.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Major Richard Wayne Brandt; and
WHEREAS, Major Richard Wayne Brandt, U.S. Air Force (ret.) was born on October 22,
1943, in Minneapolis, Minnesota, to Francis and Clarice Brandt; and
WHEREAS, he received a bachelor's degree from St. Cloud State University in
Minnesota and a Master of Arts degree in Executive Development for Public Service from Ball
State University; and
WHEREAS, Major Richard Brandt served his nation with the utmost integrity and valor
for twenty years before officially retiring with the rank of major; and
WHEREAS, he was also employed for fifteen years by the U.S. Army Civil Service as a
drug and alcohol psychologist; and
WHEREAS, Major Brandt spent most of his government service time overseas in
Germany; while there, he was an avid volksmarcher, having walked more than the equivalent
distance of the circumference of the earth (47,004 kilometers/29,206 miles); and
WHEREAS, an active member of the Parkinson's music support group, the Trembling
Troubadours, Major Richard Brandt had a lifelong love of Southern Gospel music; and
WHEREAS, a man of abiding faith, Major Brandt was a member of Delray Baptist
Church in Rossville, Georgia, which he served faithfully for many years as a deacon; and
WHEREAS, he was also deeply devoted to his family, and he always endeavored to
remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, left to cherish his memory are his loving wife of fifty-three years, Rose
Brandt; daughter, Julie Stansel; sisters, Barbara Rudlang and Rhonda Schulte; brothers-in-law,
